<br>
to me a guild is...<br>
<br>
1) family/friends<br>
2) people who will go out of their way for each other.<br>
3) a place where events are planned for the entire groups enjoyment.<br>
<br>
truth is to me it is all of these things and more.<br>
<br>
it is when someone leaves  the heart ache you feel.<br>
<br>
When someone leaves even if only with their primary it is a hurt. you know you can send them a tell when you get on. but it is not the same as that Hello across guildsay.<br>
<br>
truth is #2 and #3 probably truly best describe a regular guild. #1 in my opinion fits only a few of them on the server.<br>
<br>
you can recruit a bunch of people fast and make a big guild. or you can recruit slower and make a big family.<br>
<br>
youll end up with some friction here and there. is going to happen any time you get a group together. the diffrence is how the two handle it.<br>
<br>
any way i cant describe what im feeling. or how i feel about the wolves. <br>
<br>
Maybe someone else can. <p><img src="http://www.mr-bandwidth.com/aegiswolves/images/personalpics/2hbpic3.jpg"><br><br>
"Quantum materiae materietur marmota monax si marmota monax materiam possit materiari?"
