<br>
We have few events.  We are a role-play guild.  But there is no pressure for anyone to do something that is not fun for *them,* and that is something I really appreciate about them.  There is a lot of freedom ... and yet, we are there for each other if needed.  It is one of the loosest looking groups, examining it from the outside ... but if you start to hang around with us, you will find we are as a tight a group of friends you will ever find.<br>
<br>
Leaving a guild with your primary ... is leaving a guild.  I still have alts in Sisterhood, Stormravens, and I think my bard is still even hanging around with an Aegis Wolves tag.  I rarely play them.  It isn't that I don't miss the other guilds, because frankly, I do ... a lot.  I have met so many people in my walks in Norrath, it is difficult for me to keep up with them.  30 people on a friends list is *nothing* ... I regularly also do /who all sister, /who all stormr, and /who all aegis ... just to see who is around.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Most of all, a guild should provide a sense of center, of home.  When I founded the Sisterhood, it was home for a long time, but then it lost that feel to me.  It is still home for many, but cannot be home for me.  Stormravens was never really &quot;comfortable&quot; in that way.  Aegis Wolves was VERY homey to me, and I still miss that feel some days.  But, as a relationship between Aziev and Shizandra developed ... it was a bit less comfortable.  It had nothing to do with how we were treated by any stretch -- it was just who we were and where we were.  AN is home for them.<br>
<br>
Sorry about the ramble, just thought it was an interesting question.   :-) <p><b><i><font color="#FFFF00">Paazabel says, "State the nature of your medical emergency."</font></i></b></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF00>- </font><a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/baegiswolves>Aegis Wolves</a><font color=#FFFF00> - </font><a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/faegiswolvestunarepack>Wolves Den - Tunare</a> <font color=#FFFF00> - </font><a href="www.mr-bandwidth.com/aegiswolves/">Home</a><font color=#FFFF00> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  